## Biggest Opportunities (files > 200 lines)

### 1. `battlefield.py` → extract **battle UI** and **music manager** (428 lines → ~200)

This is the largest file. It mixes **rendering**, **state machine logic**, **music management**, and **victory/defeat panels** all in one function.

| What to extract | New module | Approx lines saved |
|-----------------|-----------|---------------------|
| Music start/stop/reload logic (repeated 5× in the file) | `core/audio_manager.py` | ~50 |
| Victory/defeat panel rendering + wait loop (lines 328–420) | `components/battle_result_panel.py` | ~100 |
| Pet stance loading & sprite updating (repeated 4×) | helper in `core/battle_loader.py` (already exists, just add a method) | ~50 |

**Duplicated music pattern** — this block appears 5 times:
```python
pygame.mixer.music.stop()
bgm_path = SETTINGS.get("BGM_PATH", "assets/esefex/bg_sfx.mp3")
pygame.mixer.music.load(bgm_path)
if SETTINGS["BGM_ENABLED"]:
    pygame.mixer.music.set_volume(SETTINGS["BGM_VOLUME"])
    pygame.mixer.music.play(-1)
```
→ Replace with `audio_manager.resume_bgm()`

